    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6d696c22_fbe46416",
        "filename": "util/linux/exception_handler_client.cc",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 41,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-24T17:23:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "DPLOG_IF. Do we need to avoid logging in this function?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 41,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 41,
        "endChar": 11
      },
      "revId": "b942e75c16ce49d64f54e34ec74e0545f43d022f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a11c0624_5a214383",
        "filename": "util/linux/exception_handler_client.cc",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 41,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-24T19:41:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I was considering whether it would be acceptable to use DLOG variants in signal handlers. It could make crash handling less reliable in debug builds (I suppose we\u0027d also need to do something to handle crashes in signal handlers), but if these system calls are failing, that might be more important to know about and this is a little more convenient than knowing when/where to inject `can_log \u003d true` as we do elsewhere.",
      "parentUuid": "6d696c22_fbe46416",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 41,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 41,
        "endChar": 11
      },
      "revId": "b942e75c16ce49d64f54e34ec74e0545f43d022f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c3de4136_4b220d3f",
        "filename": "util/linux/exception_handler_client.cc",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 41,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-24T19:45:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Maybe something weaker than a DLOG? Perhaps only logging when running tests?",
      "parentUuid": "a11c0624_5a214383",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 41,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 41,
        "endChar": 11
      },
      "revId": "b942e75c16ce49d64f54e34ec74e0545f43d022f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "bff71038_7b68ba53",
        "filename": "util/linux/exception_handler_client.cc",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 41,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-24T19:58:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Maybe something weaker than a DLOG? Perhaps only logging when running tests?\n\nIf you want to press on as-is, I’d buy your “DLOG isn’t in release/production” argument as a justification to hang on to this.\n\nIn similar cases in Chrome, we’ve got RAW_LOG, which is essentially write(STDERR_FILENO, …). ’Course, here, you’d want to put the write() through LSS too.",
      "parentUuid": "c3de4136_4b220d3f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 41,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 41,
        "endChar": 11
      },
      "revId": "b942e75c16ce49d64f54e34ec74e0545f43d022f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
